description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent and Bank positions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working pattern: Seven day period, shifts 7.30 – 15.30 13.30 -21.30 21.00- 8.00&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whitchurch Community Hospital is the largest Community Hospital site within Shropshire Community Health NHS Trust. With over 600 admissions per year this is a busy ward proving high quality rehabilitation, step up/down provision, palliative and end of life care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a motivated, Staff Nurse to join our busy Community Hospital at Whitchurch. The hospital has 32 beds with an additional capacity for 4 escalation beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and innovate nurse with clinical expertise and decision making skills to deliver safe and effective patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have the opportunity to work with a highly experienced Multi-disciplinary Team ensuring the patient’s rehabilitation journey is individualised and goals are achieved to reach their maximum potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have an opportunity to build on your clinical and rehabilitation skills and there will be learning and development opportunities for the right candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to become part of our successful clinical team we would welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 25th to 26th November 2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit please contact: Nikki Ryder, Ward Manager on 01948 666292.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
